      <t:body>
         <t:listPerson>
            <t:person sex="2">
               <t:persName xml:id="n1" xml:lang="am">ድንቅነሽ፡ ምርጫ፡</t:persName>
               <t:persName corresp="#n1" xml:lang="am" type="normalized">Dǝnqǝnaš Mǝrč̣ā</t:persName>
               <t:persName><t:roleName type="title">ʾǝtege</t:roleName></t:persName>
               <t:occupation type="political"/>
               <t:birth when="1833"/>
               <t:floruit>
                 Dǝnqǝnaš Mǝrč̣ā was first married to <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4258GabraKi"> Gäbrä Kidan Zemo </t:persName> from whom she had
                 a son, <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8799seyyum"> Śǝyyum “Abba Gobäz” </t:persName>, and three daughters,
                 <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1996Aradacc"> Aradäčč Gäbrä Kidan </t:persName>, <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9132Takkolac"> Täkkoläčč Gäbrä Kidan </t:persName>, and
                 <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2759BezuGab"> Bǝzu Gäbrä Kidan </t:persName>. After the divorce, she married
                 <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9143TaklaGi">Gobaze Gabra Madḫǝn</t:persName> in <t:date>1867</t:date>. The latter proclaimed himself
                  ʾaṣe Takla Giyorgis II in <t:date>1867</t:date>, thus Dǝnqǝnaš Mǝrč̣ā received a title of ʾǝtege. After the defeat of her
                  husband, she joined him in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1398AmbaSa">Amba Sälama</t:placeName> and stayed with him until his death. Thereafter,
                  she moved to the Imperial Court and became one of the most influential advisors of her brother
                  <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">ʾaṣe Yoḥannǝs IV</t:persName>. After the banishment and death of her son
                  <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8799seyyum"> Śǝyyum “Abba Gobäz” </t:persName>, she retreated to <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5749Sire">Šire</t:placeName>.
               </t:floruit>
               <t:death when="1912"/>
            </t:person>
         </t:listPerson>
